FBIS4-20933 "jptac004__l94008" JPRS-TAC-94-004-L JPRS Arms Control 22 April 1994 EAST EUROPE SLOVAKIA Inspection Confirms Dismantling of 44 Tanks Inspection Confirms Dismantling of 44 Tanks AU0704080394 Prague CTK in English 1940 GMT 6 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU0704080394 Prague CTK English BFN [Text] Bratislava, April 6 (CTK) -- A NATO inspection team confirmed today that Slovakia has dismantled 44 tanks in accordance with an international treaty on reducing the number of conventional weapons in Europe. According to a Vienna Convention on Reducing Conventional Arms in Europe, Slovakia must dismantle 423 tanks by November 1995. One of the 44 tanks was not dismantled or disarmed, but is destined for display in a museum. According to the agreement, next year the Slovak Army should have 46,667 soldiers, 478 combat tanks, 683 armored vehicles, 383 artillery pieces, 115 combat aircraft, and 25 combat helicopters.
